ject": {}}], "So, if Red Bull get Perez's car fixed up, he's in.": [{"subject": [{"team": "Bull"}], "action": "fix", "object": {}}, {"subject": [{"driver": "PER"}], "action": "be", "object": {"main": ["So", "in"]}}], "So, Perez won't be permitted to start from the grid - but it doesn't say he can't start the race from the pitlane...": [{"subject": [{"driver": "PER"}], "action": "start", "object": {"main": ["from grid"]}}, {"subject": [{"driver": "PER"}], "action": "start n't", "object": {"main": ["race", "from pitlane"]}}], "Motorsport.com F1 editor Jon Noble has dug out a key regulation:\nArticle 38.1: Any car which does not complete a reconnaissance lap and reach the grid under its own power will not be permitted to start the race from the grid.": [{"subject": [{"driver": "Noble"}], "action": "dig", "object": {"main": ["key regulation"]}}], "Michael Masi says that the three-hour window allotted for the race began at 1500 local time, so we'll have a timed race if we get going.": [{"subject": [{"driver": "Masi"}], "action": "begin", "object": {"main": ["at 1500 local time"]}}], "If Perez's car gets fixed, it looks as though he'll be allowed to start. Mercedes sporting director Ron Meadows seemed a little puzzled by that outcome.": [{"subject": [{"driver": "PER"}], "action": "start", "object": {}}, {"subject": [{"driver": "Meadows"}], "action": "seem", "object": {}}], "Our news editor Tom Howard also has some stats to chat:\u00a0Michael Schumacher is the most successful driver in Belgium with a total of six wins. Ayrton Senna is his closest challenger with five triumphs.": [{"subject": [{"driver": "MSC"}], "action": "have", "object": {"main": ["stats to chat"]}}, {"subject": [{"driver": "Senna"}], "action": "be", "object": {"main": ["closest challenger"]}}], "Another big fact from the desk of Mr. Turner:\u00a0\nBefore Esteban Ocon's Hungarian GP victory, you had to go back to Daniel Ricciardo's 2014 win at the Hungaroring to find a rain-affected race win scored by so